com.versant.odmg
Interface Bag

All Superinterfaces:
Collection
public interface Bag
extends Collection

ODMG 2.0 Java Binding defines the Interface Bag. A Bag is an unordered collection of persistent objects and can contain duplicate objects.

See also the following methods in the Collection Interface:

See Also:
Collection.add(Object), Collection.contains(Object), Collection.elements(), Collection.existsElement(String), Collection.isEmpty(), Collection.query(String), Collection.remove(Object), Collection.select(String), Collection.selectElement(String), Collection.size()

Method Detail

put

java.lang.Object put(java.lang.Object object)
Put object in this Bag.

Parameters:
object - The object to add.

If the object does not exist in this Bag, add the object and return null.

If the object does exist, replace the first object that matches with the new object and return the old object.

Throws:
java.lang.NullPointerException - if object is equal to null
